== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=5141fba3-695a-4d7f-8b3f-8824a7a0d106.jpg|hovertext=Photo_Generated_By_BackAI.Archiv-V2|caption=A graphic that attempts to represent the default appearance of the level.}}'''Level 419's''' default appearance features an enormous, aqua-colored area, complete with blueprints for flooring, ceilings, and walls. The size of the room can range from 5 m to 50 km, depending on the current layout of the level. Each wall displays a blueprint-like design, with beams of blue light shooting across. It’s rumored that if you touch these beams, you can be electrocuted, though this is not yet confirmed.

Most of the time, this room cannot be experienced or is difficult to see. This is due to an effect called '''“Mnemonic Reconstruction,”''' which causes the room and all aspects of it (like colors, forms, etc.) to constantly be changing, making the person wandering into this room feel as if they are inside a reconstructed world. This false world created by the phenomenon is based solely on the memories and experiences of the person wandering through the room. Therefore, regardless of how extravagant a memory it is, it will always resemble something familiar to the wanderer, such as a former home, city, school, or even a country they once traveled to.

There are certain limitations to memory based on the things that explorers are unable to recollect or experience. If an explorer falls into the level, they cannot return to locations they had never visited before, as the environment can only reconstruct places they remember. Most of the time, the recreated memories cannot show what happened in the place before it was explored. But, sometimes, [[Entity 9|Facelings]] have been seen walking around, often acting like important people from the explorer’s life.

In these memories, it normally feels as if you are directly inside them, always with the same lighting and time as when the memory originally occurred. They also carry a scent very similar to that moment. For example, if the memory takes place in a steak restaurant, there will be a strong smell of meat. This applies to every recreated memory. The level can also generate a feeling of melancholy in the wanderer inside it. Many people have said it feels as if you are directly reliving that same memory.{{Blurimage|file=ojopiojo.png|hovertext='''''<u>ERROR_THIS_SHOULD_NOT_BE_HERE</u>'''''|caption=A low-quality photo found of one of the cracks|align=Left}}A wanderer cannot decide which memory to go to when they enter the level. The first time they arrive in the level, they can be fooled into thinking that they have escaped the Backrooms and returned [[The Frontrooms|Home]]. Photographs can be taken inside the level. Unfortunately, photos taken inside the level often have a blue tint. This colour distortion makes them harder to see clearly. Despite these challenges, you may still be able to discern what is in the photograph.

It has been noted that the walls may exhibit structural anomalies (such as cracks) in certain locations within the level. Cracks in the walls will reveal a light blue wall with a blueprint texture similar to how the level looks normally. These cracks will last anywhere from 2 to 5 hours and typically expand before eventually sealing up. Memory shifts can occur so suddenly that the wanderer may fail to notice them at firs. In most cases, the new memory appears very similar to the last memory and could even happen in the same place, at the same time, or as part of the same incident. Very rarely does this happen and evolve into something completely different than previous memories. The impact of these memory changes can result in severe headaches, dizziness, nausea, and chills for the explorer.

Although the cracks can be felt without causing any harm, when you touch one, it will ruin your memory. This will cause the current memory to break apart and switch to another, or briefly reveal the level's default appearance. There may also be a temporary chill or headache immediately after touching the crack as well, but that will go away after a while. In very rare instances, someone may actually faint from touching a crack. None of these effects has been shown to cause permanent damage.

== Entities ==
'''Level 419''' contains a few entities. The only known entities actively found within this level include the [[Entity 9|facelings]], which have typically been reported to appear, behave, or act similarly to the individuals that existed within that memory, including their same mannerisms and appearance (e.g., clothing, skin, etc.). They will always stay in their roles. Even when physically pushed or hit, facelings keep showing the memory, ignoring any outside interference. They seem to be unaware of the person, which is why facelings are often seen in places where memories usually wouldn't be found, like behind walls.

No other entities have been observed in the level so far...

