==Cognitive Effects==
In addition to the phenomenon known as '''Mnemonic Reconstruction''', '''Level 419''' exhibits numerous cognitive effects associated with it. Some examples of these effects can be as simple as feeling very comfortable while being in some of the recreated memories you experience; some also give Wanderers the desire to stay in the level for all eternity. Many will find themselves feeling calm, relaxed, and unusually content while immersed in these recreated memories. There are other commonly reported effects as well, such as persistent dizziness and nausea. In rare instances, there have also been occurrences of hallucinations associated with the level. The longer a person remains within Level 419, the more pronounced these effects tend to become.

A number of people have mentioned how, as time goes on inside '''Level 419''', they feel as if their memories are being rebuilt and relived. Yet, over time, they also report feeling less human. Wanderers have described sensations of slowing down mentally, feeling emotionally distant from others, and experiencing a gradual loss of emotional response, as though they are slowly transitioning from human to something more mechanical. Some reports describe this effect as if a machine were repairing or modifying them in some way. As if their former selves were no longer sufficient, and what they now require is to change — to become something capable of observing, processing, and generating memories.

'''Because memories... may be the last thing of value left.'''

