==Unstable Structure==
{{Blurimage|file=blueerror.png|hovertext=ERROR_Textures_Bad_Memory_N012|caption=Photo showing structural errors}}
Besides the cracks, '''Level 419''' also has many other types of structural abnormalities that could potentially be hazardous. Most of these structural discrepancies are attributed to the phenomenon of '''mnemonic reconstruction'''. Some of the most typical structural discrepancies appear as direct ruptures in a memory. This phenomenon can leave large areas within the walls without their illusion, exposing the '''default''' surface appearance behind the wall. These memory ruptures are much more dangerous than typical wall cracks because if they are touched, a significant electric shock (as high as 30 mA) can be released, resulting in respiratory failure. The structural anomalies observed in Level 419 suggest that this level may function as an electronic or mechanical system in which all objects within the level are directly part of the machine or in which a much larger electrical or mechanical system exists that controls the environment.

A second type of structural anomaly exists with non-collision walls, which may be moved through contact alone. They can exist anywhere in a memory, including on the floor, ceiling, or normal walls. Although you can move through one of these walls, you should not; passing through one will usually cause an immediate change in memory, resulting in dizziness and/or nausea. Because of the small chance of the wall colliding again while someone is inside, a person could be split in half or lose their hands, knees, or feet, or even their head. Additionally, records show that when a memory includes an electronic device, the screens of that device might sometimes display an unknown logo. The logo contains text, but some of the text is not easily identifiable; however, identified words are like '''generate''', '''repair''', '''remember''', and '''memory'''.

One uncommon problem in the structure is the merging of two different memories. The overlapping of two different memories produces two different areas that will become intertwined and create areas that are distorted. In one case, it was noted that if two [[Entity 9|Facelings]] were to interact with each other inside an area that was overlapping, both Facelings would explode violently because both had been occupying the same area.

